name: guanylthiourea
Reason: 1,2-thiadiazole ring introduces additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions and potentially hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by about +70°C. The presence of a methoxy group can also increase the melting point due to the increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces, estimated at around +10°C.
